added.title: Stickiest Situation
added.description: Sticky Joe loses his shoe and his search takes him on another wild adventure.

added.title: O.S.H.A.
added.description: The Titans must clean the Tower for a surprise inspection.

added.title: Teen? Titans
added.description: When the Titans' real ages are revealed they must think and act like teenages to remain Teen Titans.

added.title: Moonlighting
added.description: Inspired by a commercial, the Titans visit Dr. Light and Dr. Moon to learn how to make extra money.

added.title: Freak Show
added.description: Control Freak tries once more to convince the Titans that the original show is the superior series.

added.title: Diner Means Breakfast
added.description: Cyborg and Beast Boy realize that what they order to eat at a diner might have much bigger consequences.

added.title: High Five
added.description: While shopping at the mall, the Titans enter a contest to win a hot tub.

added.title: Teen Titans and the Easter Factory
added.description: Will a trip to the Eastory Factory be a magical time for the Titans or is it another one of the Easter Bunny's tricks?

added.title: Passive Income
added.description: Lex Luthor buys the Titans' island and shows them how to make passive income through real estate.

added.title: Friendship
added.description: Zapped into an episode of Pretty Pretty Pegasus, the Titans must fight their way out using love and friendship.

added.title: The Mask
added.description: Robin's mask doesn't just conceal his secret identity, it hides a terrible secret!

added.title: Serious Business
added.description: The Titans learn the hard way what a bathroom is really for.

added.title: Boys vs Girls
added.description: The Titans try to settle the eternal question: Are boys or girls better?

added.title: Body Adventure
added.description: When Cyborg is sick, Robin insists on shrinking to cell size to fight Cyborg's infection himself.

added.title: Road Trip
added.description: A road trip in Cyborg's T-Car is really fun - for a while.

added.title: Halloween
added.description: Raven tries to put the spirit of Halloween back in Halloween.

added.title: Sandwich Thief
added.description: Robin's perfect sandwich is missing and he will stop at nothing to find it.

added.title: Vegetables
added.description: The Titans try vegetarianism, but learn that not everyone is cut out for that lifestyle.

added.title: Thanksgiving
added.description: When Raven's father Trigon shows up for Thanksgiving dinner, Robin's seating plan isn't the only thing that gets ruined.

added.title: Creepy Crawler Creature Catcher
added.description: The hottest new game just got real. A cybervillain unleashes giant versions of the game's digital creepy crawlies across Singapore, landing the spies deep in cyber-slime. Will the spies make it through in time for Glitterstar's mysterious invitation?

added.title: What Woolly Mammoth
added.description: The Spies are sent on a chilly mission to stop a villain who has brought woolly mammoths back to life, but can they bring down the nefarious knitter before the Earth is sent back to the Ice Age? Brrr!

added.title: A Bully for Bugs/The Wheel Deal
added.description: A Bully for Bugs: With Floyd's adult assistance, Baby Bugs and the Baby Looney Tunes learn an effective way to deal with a bully. /The Wheel Deal: Everyone's excited about a grand bicycle outing through the park, everyone except Tweety whose little legs don't quite reach the pedals. Frustrated after riding on the back of Floyd's bicycle while everyone else has fun, Tweety is ready to go home.

added.title: Oh Brother, Warehouse Art Thou?/Flu the Coop
added.description: Oh, Brother, Warehouse Art Thou?: Baby Sylvester is overcome with angst because Granny's broken old chair, his favorite napping place, must be replaced by a new, unfamiliar piece of furniture. The other Baby Looney Tunes work together to help turn Sylvester's trepidation into enjoyment during their mammoth furniture-shopping adventure./Flu the Coop: Baby Bugs and Baby Daffy decide to team up and unlike the other Baby Looney Tunes, fake having received their annual flu shots at the local clinic. The joke's on them when they awaken on the day of Granny's big party unable to have fun because they both have the flu.

added.title: Blast Off Bugs/Baby Brouhaha
added.description: Blastoff Bugs: Baby Bugs tries to realize his dream of traveling to the moon while the Baby Looney Tunes are on a space museum visit./Baby Brouhaha: Overhearing Granny on the phone say she's expecting a baby, Baby Bugs goes into overdrive, revving up the Baby Looney Tunes to prepare to care for an infant.

added.title: Log Cabin Fever/A Mid-Autumn Night's Scream
added.description: Log Cabin Fever: Granny takes the Baby Looney Tunes back to a simpler lifestyle during a rustic weekend spent in an 1800's log cabin, where they learn to enjoy life minus all modern conveniences. Baby Bugs and Baby Daffy get in trouble for smuggling their palm-sized computer game along, and they face Granny's consequences./A Mid-Autumn Night's Scream: The Baby Looney Tunes first Halloween involves a costume contest for Lola, Melissa and Petunia, group trick-or-treating and Sylvester overcoming his fear of confronting an allegedly scary neighbor.

added.title: Are We There Yet/Save Our Cinnamon
added.description: Are We There, Yet?: During a long road trip, Floyd, obsessed with taking the Baby Looney Tunes to visit the distant, annual Acme Garlic Festival, endures countless variants of the universal kid question, are we there, yet? Despite Floyd's garlic agenda, fate has other plans./Save Our Cinnamon: Granny's sister's beloved bakery, Cakery Bakery Dock, home of her wonderful trademark cinnamon rolls, is being put out of business so her landlord can tear down the bakery to build a parking lot. This galvanizes the Baby Looney Tunes to work together to bake one giant cinnamon roll as a tourist attraction to save the bakery, a project that ends up involving the whole town.
